    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="434"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.304M28/71.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 165.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith
                        enclosed<note n="1" xml:id="d434fn1">Not printed.</note> translation of
                    newspaper comment concerning the wreck of the <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi> and
                    the honors to the victims. * * *</p>
                <p>I have not ventured to report the ceremonies themselves in the belief that a full
                    report will be made to the War and Navy Departments by the officers directly
                    concerned.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. M. Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
